Welcome to the Permit Tracker.

Start by selecting the Jurisdiction with the authority to approve the permit.

If this is the first permit in an area, Add a new Jurisdiction record.

Click the pencil icon to view Jurisdiction details.

After selecting the Jurisdiction, Click APPLY to create the Permit record.

Permit Status is updated by OneVizion Automation:

Approved - the permit approved finish date is entered

Expired - the permit expirtion date is in the past and construction has not started*

Cancelled - the permit cancelled checkbox is checked

Rejected - the permit rejected checkbox is checked

Expires before Cx Start - the expiration date occurs before the construction start date*

Submitted - Application Submitted date has been entered and has not been approved or rejected

In Progress - the permit has not been submitted; enter the Application Submitted date.

*requires Permit to be a child to the Project Tracker and links to the project workplan.
